get_row_col <- function(fdr, start, fac_matrix) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    70x
                    
                      
  cell    <- terra::cellFromXY(fdr, start)

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    70x
                    
                      
  row_col <- terra::rowColFromCell(fdr, cell)

                    		
                  

                  

                    363
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    364
                    70x
                    
                      
  neighbors <- get_neighbor_df(row_col[1], row_col[2],

                    		
                  

                  

                    365
                    70x
                    
                      
                               nrow(fac_matrix), ncol(fac_matrix))

                    		
                  

                  

                    366
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    367
                    70x
                    
                      
  neighbor_fac <- fac_matrix[cbind(neighbors$row, neighbors$col)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    368
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    369
                    
                    
                      
  # Some flowline outlets don't hit the right raster cell.

                    		
                  

                  

                    370
                    
                    
                      
  # This grabs a neighbor that is more than twice the flow accumulation

                    		
                  

                  

                    371
                    
                    
                      
  # to avoid just going 1 cell in the downstream direction.

                    		
                  

                  

                    372
                    70x
                    
                      
  if (any(neighbor_fac > (fac_matrix[row_col[1], row_col[2]]) * 2)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    373
                    28x
                    
                      
    new_rc <- neighbors[which(neighbor_fac == max(neighbor_fac)), 1:2]

                    		
                  

                  

                    374
                    28x
                    
                      
    row_col[1] <- new_rc$row

                    		
                  

                  

                    375
                    28x
                    
                      
    row_col[2] <- new_rc$col

                    		
                  

                  

                    376
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    377
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    378
                    70x
                    
                      
  return(row_col)

                    		
                  

                  

                    379
                    
                    
                      
}

trace_downstream <- function(start_point, fdr, distance = 10000) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    458
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    459
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    460
                    1x

                    461
                    !

                    476

    # next local flow direction from matrix

#' Build a new ID lookup table

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' @param gpkgs a row of network metadata built with `network_metadata`

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' @param flowpath_layer the layer name containing flowpaths

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' @param divide_layer the layer name containing divides

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a data.frame with the file.path, file name, VPU,flowpath count, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' divides count, cumulative flowpath count and cumulative divides count

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

#' @importFrom dplyr select mutate left_join

build_new_id_table = function(x, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
                              flowpath_layer = "flowpaths",

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
                              divide_layer   = "divides"){

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    4x
                    
                      
  div = read_sf(x$path, divide_layer) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    4x
                    
                      
    renamer()

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    4x
                    
                      
  fl = read_sf(x$path, flowpath_layer) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    4x
                    
                      
    st_drop_geometry() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    4x
                    
                      
    renamer()

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    4x
                    
                      
  if("set" %in% names(fl)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    2x
                    
                      
    fl <- select(fl, oldID = id, set)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    2x
                    
                      
    fl = select(fl, oldID = id, member_comid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    4x
                    
                      
  data.frame(oldID = sort(div$id)) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    4x
                    
                      
    mutate(newID = 1:length(unique(div$id)) + x$cumcount_div,

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
           #newID = ifelse(oldID < 0, newID * -1, newID),

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    4x
                    
                      
           newID = ifelse(oldID == 0, 0, newID),

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    4x
                    
                      
           VPU = x$VPU) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    4x
                    
                      
    left_join(fl, by = "oldID")

}

#' Update Network Identifiers

                    		
                  

                  

                    70

update_topo = function(x, lookup, vpu_topo = NULL){

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    20x
                    
                      
  if("id" %in% names(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    18x
                    
                      
    x$id = lookup$newID[match(x$id, lookup$oldID)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    20x
                    
                      
  if("toid" %in% names(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    16x
                    
                      
    x$toid = lookup$newID[match(x$toid, lookup$oldID)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    16x
                    
                      
    x$toid[is.na(x$toid)] = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    20x
                    
                      
  if((nrow(vpu_topo) != 0 | is.null(vpu_topo)) & "toid" %in% names(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
    good = filter(x, !id %in% vpu_topo$ID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    fix  = filter(x,   id %in% vpu_topo$ID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !

                    98
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
    x = bind_rows(good, fix)

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    20x
                    
                      
  if("id" %in% names(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    18x
                    
                      
    x$id = as.integer(x$id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    20x
                    
                      
  if("toid" %in% names(x)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    16x
                    
                      
    x$toid = as.integer(x$toid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    20x
                    
                      
  x

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Aggregate Network

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Aggregates a catchment network according to a set of outlet.

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param flowpath sf data.frame Flowpaths with ID, toID, LevelPathID, and Hydroseq attributes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outlets data.frame with "ID" and "type" columns. "ID" must be identifiers from

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' flowpath and divide data.frames. "type" should be "outlet", or "terminal".

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' "outlet" will include the specified ID.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' "terminal" will be treated as a terminal node with nothing downstream.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param da_thresh numeric Defaults to NA. A threshold total drainage area in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' units of the TotDASqKM

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' field of the flowpath data.frame. When automatically adding confluences to make

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' the network valid, tributary catchments under this threshold will be lumped with

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' the larger tributaries rather than being added to the set of output catchments.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @param only_larger boolean Defaults to TRUE. If TRUE when adding confluences to

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' make the network valid, only tributaries larger than the one with an upstream

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' outlet will be added. e.g. if a tributary is required in the model this will

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' add main stems that the tributary contributes to. Note that the NHDPlus treats

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' divergences as part of the main stem, so the da_thresh may still be needed to

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' eliminate small tributary catchments introduced by divergences near confluences.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @param post_mortem_file rda file to dump environment to in case of error

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @details This function operates on the catchment network as a node-edge graph.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' The outlet types are required to ensure that graph searches start from the

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' appropriate nodes and includes the appropriate catchments. Outlets such as gages

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' should be treated as "outlet" outlets.

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' While it may be possible for the algorithm to determine terminal outlets, at this

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' time, it is required that they be specified explicitely as "terminal" outlet types.

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' The function checks supplied outlets to make sure they connect downstream. Checks

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' verify that the outlet of the levelpath (main stem of a total catchment) of each

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' supplied outlet is

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' in the supplied outlet set. If the outlet of a levelpath is not in the supplied set, it

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' is added along with other catchments that contribute to the same receiving catchment.

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' These checks ensure that all output catchments have one and only one input and output

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' nexus and that all catchments are well-connected.

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom sf st_is_empty st_drop_geometry

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr filter mutate left_join select distinct case_when bind_rows slice_min

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#' source(system.file("extdata", "walker_data.R", package = "nhdplusTools"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#' fline <- dplyr::right_join(dplyr::select(walker_flowline, COMID),

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#'                            nhdplusTools::prepare_nhdplus(walker_flowline, 0, 0, 0, FALSE))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
#' fline <- dplyr::select(fline, ID = COMID, toID = toCOMID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#'                        LevelPathID = LevelPathI, Hydroseq)

#' outlets <- data.frame(ID = c(5329357, 5329317, 5329365, 5329303, 5329435, 5329817),

sort_outlets <- function(outlets, flowpath) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    348
                    
                    
                      
  # set toID to negative the ID for terminals that are not 0.

                    		
                  

                  

                    349
                    
                    
                      
  # This is important to make sure that all outlet nexues have a unique ID

                    		
                  

                  

                    350
                    
                    
                      
  # as opposed to 0 or na. This is meangful when sorting the graph

                    		
                  

                  

                    351
                    13x
                    
                      
  flowpath$toNexID <- ifelse(flowpath$toID == 0, -flowpath$ID, flowpath$toID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    352
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    353
                    
                    
                      
  # this is a little awkward and nuanced -- read comments carefully.

                    		
                  

                  

                    354
                    13x
                    
                      
  outlets <- outlets %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    355
                    
                    
                      
    # the nexID_stem is just the catchment identifier. Conceptually,

                    		
                  

                  

                    356
                    
                    
                      
    # this is the identifier for the nearest upstream nexus from an outlet.

                    		
                  

                  

                    357
                    
                    
                      
    # We have to use this identifier for an outlet along the flowpath

                    		
                  

                  

                    358
                    
                    
                      
    # of a catchment. It can be the same as the catchment because we are

                    		
                  

                  

                    359
                    
                    
                      
    # working with a dendritic assumption so each nexus has one and only

                    		
                  

                  

                    360
                    
                    
                      
    # one downstream catchment. Otherwise, we would have to treat things a

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    
                    
                      
    # bit differently.

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    13x
                    
                      
    mutate(nexID_stem = .data$ID) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    363
                    
                    
                      
    # the nexID_terminal is the  to nexus of the terminal flowpath.

                    		
                  

                  

                    364
                    
                    
                      
    # We need to treat this differently because an outlet of type

                    		
                  

                  

                    365
                    
                    
                      
    # "terminal" must be downstream of all other outlets. Without a

                    		
                  

                  

                    366
                    
                    
                      
    # unique nexus ID like this, we can not be gaurunteed a sort

                    		
                  

                  

                    367
                    
                    
                      
    # order that will work correctly.

                    		
                  

                  

                    368
                    13x
                    
                      
    left_join(select(drop_geometry(flowpath), .data$ID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    369
                    13x
                    
                      
                     nexID_terminal = .data$toNexID), by = "ID") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    370
                    
                    
                      
    # Now we can set the nexID (which is used to sort the outlets) appropriately.

                    		
                  

                  

                    371
                    13x
                    
                      
    mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    372
                    13x
                    
                      
      nexID = case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    373

#' Aggregate Catchments

aggregate_to_outlets <- function(gpkg = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
                                 flowpath = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
                                 divide = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
                                 outlets = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
                                 zero_order = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
                                 coastal_cats = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
                                 da_thresh = NA, only_larger = FALSE, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
                                 post_mortem_file = NA, keep = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    10x
                    
                      
  network_list = read_hydrofabric(gpkg, catchments = divide, flowpaths = flowpath)

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    10x
                    
                      
  in_crs <- st_crs(network_list$catchments)

                    52
                    10x

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
    warning("found MULTIPOLYGONs in divides. They must be of type POLYGON.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list$catchments <- clean_geometry(network_list$catchments, ID = "ID", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
                             crs = in_crs, keep = NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    10x
                    
                      
  if(!is.null(zero_order)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
    if(is.null(coastal_cats)) stop("must supply coastal_cats with zero order")

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    if(st_crs(coastal_cats) != in_crs) st_transform(coastal_cats, in_crs)

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    1x
                    
                      
    zero_flowpath <- filter(network_list$flowpaths, member_COMID %in% do.call(c, zero_order))

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    1x
                    
                      
    network_list$flowpaths <- filter(network_list$flowpaths, !ID %in% zero_flowpath$ID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    1x
                    
                      
    coastal <- lapply(zero_order, function(x, coastal_cats, divide) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    2x
                    
                      
      zero_cats <- filter(coastal_cats, FEATUREID %in% x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    2x
                    
                      
      zero_div <- filter(network_list$catchments, member_COMID %in% as.character(x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    2x

                    1x

                    76
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    1x
                    
                      
    coastal <- st_sfc(coastal, crs = in_crs)

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    1x
                    
                      
    coastal <- st_sf(ID = names(coastal), geom = coastal)

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    9x
                    
                      
    coastal <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    10x
                    
                      
  if(any(remove_head_div <- !network_list$flowpaths$ID %in% network_list$flowpaths$toID &

                    10x

                    86
                    3x

                    87
                    3x

                    88
                    3x
                    
                      
                  "headwater/diversion flowlines without catchments."))

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    3x

                    90
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    10x
                    
                      
  agg_network <- aggregate_network_to_outlets(network_list$flowpaths, outlets, da_thresh, only_larger, post_mortem_file)

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    10x
                    
                      
  agg_network$cat_sets <- 

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
               # setID defines which catchments go in which aggregate catchments.

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    10x
                    
                      
    data.frame(setID = unlist(agg_network$cat_sets$set),

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
               # ID is the ID of the set brought in from aggregate network.

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    10x
                    
                      
               ID = rep(agg_network$cat_sets$ID, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    10x
                    
                      
                        times = lengths(agg_network$cat_sets$set))) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    10x
                    
                      
    left_join(select(network_list$catchments, ID), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    10x
                    
                      
              by = c("setID" = "ID")) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    10x
                    
                      
    st_as_sf() %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    10x
                    
                      
    filter(!sf::st_is_empty(.)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    10x
                    
                      
    union_polygons(ID = "ID") %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    10x
                    
                      
    clean_geometry(ID = "ID", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    10x
                    
                      
                   crs = in_crs, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    10x
                    
                      
                   keep = keep) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    10x
                    
                      
    select(.data$ID) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    10x
                    
                      
    left_join(agg_network$cat_sets, by = "ID")

                    		
                  

                  

                    110

}

prepare_network = function(network_list) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    !

                    15
                    !
                    
                      
  names(network_list$catchments) = tolower(names(network_list$catchments))

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    !
                    
                      
  if(any(duplicated(network_list$catchments))){

                    		
                  

                  

                    18

                    23

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
  if(any(duplicated(network_list$flowpaths))){

                    		
                  

                  

                    26

    n = sum(duplicated(network_list$flowpaths))

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
    id = network_list$flowpaths$id[which(duplicated(network_list$flowpaths))]

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
  if(any(duplicated(network_list$flowpaths$id))){

                    		
                  

                  

                    34

    n = sum(duplicated(network_list$flowpaths))

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    hyaggregate_log("WARN", glue("Dropping {n} duplicate flowpaths."))

                    		
                  

                  

                    36

#' Check Network Validity

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
#' Validates a flowpath and catchment network

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
#' @param term_cut cutoff integer to define terminal IDs

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a list containing flowline and catchment `sf` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr mutate select left_join

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom sf st_drop_geometry

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
check_network_validity     <- function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
                                       term_cut = 1e9,

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
                                       check = TRUE){

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths = network_list$flowpaths

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
  cat       = network_list$catchments

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
  names(flowpaths) = tolower(names(flowpaths))

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
  names(cat) = tolower(names(cat))

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths$toid    = ifelse(is.na(flowpaths$toid), 0, flowpaths$toid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
  if(!check){ return(list(flowpaths = fl, catchments = cat))}

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
  DAG               = network_is_dag(flowpaths)

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
  CONNECTION        = sum(!(flowpaths$toid %in% flowpaths$id | flowpaths$toid > term_cut | flowpaths$toid == 0)) == 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
  if(all(DAG,  CONNECTION)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
    return(list(flowpaths = flowpaths, catchments = cat))

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
    if(!DAG){ stop("Network is not a graph.")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    if(!CONNECTION){stop("All toIDs are not present in network.")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    98

#' Check if network is DAG

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
#' Checks in a `sf` flowline network is a DAG (Directed acyclic graph).

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fl a LINESTRING `sf` flowlines object

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ID the name of the ID column in `fl`

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    
                    
                      
#' @param toID the name of the toID column in `fl`

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      
#' @return boolean

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom igraph graph_from_data_frame is.dag

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom sf st_drop_geometry

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr select

                    		
                  

                  

                    109

network_is_dag = function(fl, ID = "id", toID = "toid"){

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
  st_drop_geometry(select(fl, !!ID, !!toID)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
    graph_from_data_frame(directed = TRUE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
    is.dag()

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
#' Add hydrosequence

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
#' @param flowpaths sf object (LINESTRING)

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
#' @return sf object

add_hydroseq = function(flowpaths) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths$terminalID = NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths$terminalid = NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths$hydroseq   = NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
  flowpaths$toid = ifelse(is.na(flowpaths$toid), 0, flowpaths$toid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    !
                    
                      
  topo = get_sorted(st_drop_geometry(select(flowpaths, id, toid)), split = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
  topo['hydroseq'] = 1:nrow(topo)

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
  left_join(flowpaths, select(topo, id, hydroseq), by = "id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
}

add_measures = function(flowpaths, cat) {

                    149

                        select(st_drop_geometry(cat), id, areasqkm),

#' Compute length in kilometers

#' @param x LINESTRING sf object

                    236

                    !
                    
                      
                    verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    242

                    !
                    
                      
    return(FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    247

    hyaggregate_log( "INFO",

                    		
                  

                  

                    248

                    !
                    
                      
                     verbose)

#' @title split lines

#' @title Reconcile Collapsed Flowlines

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Reconciles output of collapse_flowlines giving a unique ID to

                    		
                  

                  

                    3

#' @param id character id collumn name.

#' @return reconciled flowpaths with new ID, toID, LevelPathID, and Hydroseq identifiers.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' Note that all the identifiers are new integer IDs. LevelPathID and Hydroseq are consistent

#' @importFrom dplyr group_by ungroup filter left_join select rename

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' mutate distinct summarise arrange desc

#' @seealso The \code{\link{refactor_nhdplus}} function implements a complete

                    		
                  

                  

                    14

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
reconcile_collapsed_flowlines <- function(flines, geom = NULL, id = "COMID") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    15x
                    
                      
  check_names(flines, "reconcile_collapsed_flowlines")

                    21
                    15x
                    
                      
  new_flines <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    15x

                    23
                    15x
                    
                      
           becomes =

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    15x
                    
                      
             ifelse((is.na(.data$joined_fromCOMID) | .data$joined_fromCOMID == -9999),

                    15x
                    
                      
                     ifelse((is.na(.data$joined_toCOMID) | .data$joined_toCOMID == -9999),

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    15x
                    
                      
                            .data$COMID, .data$joined_toCOMID),

                    15x
                    
                      
                    .data$joined_fromCOMID))

                    29

                    31
                    15x
                    
                      
  joined_from <- new_flines[new_flines$joined_fromCOMID %in% new_flines$becomes, ]

                    15x
                    
                      
  joined_to   <- new_flines[new_flines$joined_toCOMID %in% new_flines$becomes, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    15x

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    15x
                    
                      
  update_tofrom <- left_join(select(joined_tofrom, .data$COMID, .data$becomes), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    15x
                    
                      
                             select(joined_from, .data$COMID, new_becomes = .data$becomes), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    38

                             by = c("becomes" = "COMID"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    40

  if(nrow(update_tofrom) > 0) {

                    1x

      select(-.data$new_becomes)

                    46
                    15x
                    
                      
  new_flines <- new_flines %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    15x
                    
                      
    group_by(.data$becomes) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    15x
                    
                      
    mutate(LENGTHKM = max(.data$LENGTHKM),

                    15x
                    
                      
           Hydroseq = min(.data$Hydroseq),

#' @title Reconcile Catchment Divides

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Reconciles catchment divides according to the output of

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
#' \code{\link{reconcile_collapsed_flowlines}} and \code{\link{refactor_nhdplus}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fline_ref sf data.frame flowlines as returned by

                    		
                  

                  

                    136

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fline_rec sf data.frame flowpaths as returned by

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fac character path to flow accumulation

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#' @param para integer numer of cores to use for parallel execution

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#' @param cache path .rda to cache incremental outputs

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fix_catchments logical. should catchment geometries be rectified?

                    		
                  

                  

                    146

                    147

                    148
