#' Add Length Map to Refactored Network

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function replicates the member_COMID column of a refactored

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      
#' network but adds a new notation Following each COMID is '.' which is proceeded

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    
                    
                      
#' by the fraction of that COMID making up the new flowpath. For example 101.1

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    
                    
                      
#' would indicate 100% of COMID 101 is in the new ID.

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    
                    
                      
#' Equally 101.05 would indicate 50% of COMID 101 is present in the new ID'd flowpath

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    
                    
                      
#' @param flowpaths a refactored flowpath network containing an member_COMID column

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    
                    
                      
#' @param length_table a table of NHDPlus COMIDs and LENGTH to use as weights.

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    
                    
                      
#' Can be found with \code{nhdplusTools::get_vaa("lengthkm")}

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    
                    
                      
#' @return sf object

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    
                    
                      
#' path <- system.file("extdata/walker_reconcile.gpkg", package = "hydrofab")

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    
                    
                      
#' fps  <- add_lengthmap(flowpaths = sf::read_sf(path),

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    
                    
                      
#' length_table = nhdplusTools::get_vaa("lengthkm"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    308
                    
                    
                      
#'@importFrom dplyr select mutate filter left_join right_join arrange group_by summarize

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    
                    
                      
#'@importFrom sf st_drop_geometry st_length st_as_sf

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    
                    
                      
#'@importFrom nhdplusTools get_vaa

                    		
                  

                  

                    311
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    312
                    
                    
                      
add_lengthmap = function(flowpaths, length_table){

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp = dplyr::select(st_drop_geometry(flowpaths),

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    !
                    
                      
                           .data$ID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    !
                    
                      
                           COMID = .data$member_COMID) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    317
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(COMID = strsplit(.data$COMID, ","))

                    		
                  

                  

                    318
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    319
                    !
                    
                      
  unnested = data.frame(ID =  rep(tmp$ID,  times = lengths(tmp$COMID)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    320
                    !
                    
                      
                    COMID = as.character(unlist(tmp$COMID)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    321
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    322
                    !
                    
                      
  unnested2 = filter(unnested, grepl("\\.", COMID)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    323
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(baseCOMID = floor(as.numeric(COMID)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    324
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    325
                    !
                    
                      
  lengthm_fp = length_table %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    326
                    !
                    
                      
    select(baseCOMID = .data$comid, .data$lengthkm) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    327
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(lengthm_fp = .data$lengthkm * 1000, lengthkm = NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    !
                    
                      
  lengthm_id = flowpaths %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(lengthm_id = as.numeric(st_length(.))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    !
                    
                      
    select(.data$ID, .data$lengthm_id) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    !
                    
                      
    st_drop_geometry()

                    		
                  

                  

                    333
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    334
                    !
                    
                      
  map = left_join(left_join(unnested2, lengthm_fp, "baseCOMID"), lengthm_id, by = "ID") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    335
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(perLength = round(.data$lengthm_id/.data$lengthm_fp, 3)/10) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    336
                    !
                    
                      
    select(.data$ID, .data$COMID, .data$perLength) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    337
                    !
                    
                      
    right_join(unnested, by = c("ID", "COMID")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    338
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(perLength = ifelse(is.na(.data$perLength), 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    339
                    !
                    
                      
                              as.character(.data$perLength))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    340
                    !
                    
                      
    arrange(.data$ID) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    341
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(new = paste0(floor(as.numeric(.data$COMID)), ".",

                    		
                  

                  

                    342

                        gsub("0\\.", "", .data$perLength))) %>%

    right_join(flowpaths) %>%

    st_as_sf()

                    349
                    
                    
                      
}

#' @title Collapse NHDPlus Network

        (rfl & (flines$toCOMID == 0)) # flows to the coast

                    		
                  

                  

                    585
                    
                    
                      
               

                    		
                  

                  

                    586
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    587
                    
                    
                      
      # remove problems from remove

                    		
                  

                  

                    588
                    69x
                    
                      
      rfl <- rfl & !ph

                    		
                  

                  

                    589
                    69x
                    
                      
      ph_index <- which(ph)

                    		
                  

                  

                    590
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    591
                    
                    
                      
      # Set broken ones to -9999 to indicate they can't be collapsed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    592
                    69x
                    
                      
      flines[["joined_toCOMID"]][ph_index] <- -9999

                    		
                  

                  

                    593
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    594
                    69x
                    
                      
      flines <- select(flines, -ds_joined_fromCOMID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    595
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    596
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    597
                    94x
                    
                      
    rfl_index <- which(rfl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    598
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    599
                    
                    
                      
    # Set joined_toCOMID for remove set.

                    		
                  

                  

                    600
                    94x
                    
                      
    flines[["joined_toCOMID"]][rfl_index] <- flines[["toCOMID"]][rfl_index]

                    		
                  

                  

                    601

    # Find index of next downstream to add length to.

                    		
                  

                  

                    603
                    94x
                    
                      
    adjust_headwater_index <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    604
                    94x
                    
                      
      match(flines[["toCOMID"]][rfl_index], flines$COMID)

                    		
                  

                  

                    605
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    606
                    94x
                    
                      
    flines[["LENGTHKM"]][adjust_headwater_index] <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    607
                    94x
                    
                      
      flines[["LENGTHKM"]][adjust_headwater_index] +

                    		
                  

                  

                    608
                    94x
                    
                      
      flines[["LENGTHKM"]][rfl_index]

                    		
                  

                  

                    609
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    610
                    
                    
                      
    # Set removed so they won't get used later.

                    		
                  

                  

                    611
                    94x
                    
                      
    flines[["LENGTHKM"]][rfl_index] <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    612
                    94x
                    
                      
    flines[["toCOMID"]][rfl_index] <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    613
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    614
                    94x
                    
                      
    if (count > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    615
                    
                    
                      
      # look for instances of COMID that are about to

                    		
                  

                  

                    616
                    
                    
                      
      # get skipped over -- fix them.

                    		
                  

                  

                    617
                    39x
                    
                      
      flines <- left_join(flines,

                    		
                  

                  

                    618
                    39x
                    
                      
                          filter(select(flines, COMID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    619
                    39x
                    
                      
                                        new_joined_toCOMID = joined_toCOMID),

                    		
                  

                  

                    620
                    39x
                    
                      
                                 !is.na(new_joined_toCOMID)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    621
                    39x
                    
                      
                          by = c("joined_toCOMID" = "COMID"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    622
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    623
                    39x
                    
                      
      flines <- mutate(flines,

                    		
                  

                  

                    624
                    39x
                    
                      
                       joined_toCOMID =

                    		
                  

                  

                    625
                    39x
                    
                      
                         ifelse((!is.na(new_joined_toCOMID) &

                    		
                  

                  

                    626
                    39x
                    
                      
                                    !new_joined_toCOMID == -9999),

                    39x
                    
                      
                                 new_joined_toCOMID,

                    		
                  

                  

                    628
                    39x
                    
                      
                                 joined_toCOMID))

                    39x
                    
                      
      flines <- select(flines, -new_joined_toCOMID)

                    94x
                    
                      
    removed_tracker <- c(removed_tracker, flines[["COMID"]][rfl_index])

                    94x
                    
                      
    count <- count + 1

                    94x
                    
                      
    if (count > 100) {

      stop("stuck in headwaters while loop")

    }

    rfl <- remove_fun(flines)

}

#' Identify intersection types and downstream topology

#' @param flowpaths sf LINESTRING

#' @return data.frame with id, type, touches, touches_toID columns

#' @importFrom nhdplusTools rename_geometry get_node

define_touch_id = function(flowpaths, term_cut = 1e9){

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp =  st_cast(flowpaths, "MULTILINESTRING")

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    !
                    
                      
  ends = tmp  %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    !
                    
                      
    nhdplusTools::rename_geometry('geometry') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
   

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(geometry = nhdplusTools::get_node(., "end")$geometry)

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
  starts_ends = bind_rows(get_node(tmp, "start"), get_node(tmp, "end"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    !
                    
                      
  emap     = st_intersects(ends, starts_ends)

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp$type = ifelse(lengths(emap) > 1, "nex", "jun")

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp$type = ifelse(tmp$toid > term_cut, "term", tmp$type)

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
  ends2 = left_join(st_drop_geometry(select(ends, id)), st_drop_geometry(select(tmp, id, type)), by = "id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
  tmap = st_intersects(ends, tmp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
  data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
    id            = rep(ends2$id, times = lengths(tmap)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
    type          = rep(ends2$type, times = lengths(tmap)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
    touches       = tmp$id[unlist(tmap)],

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
    touches_toID  = tmp$toid[unlist(tmap)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  ) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
}

#' @title Build Headwater Collapse Table

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' @description  Identifies small (pathlength or area) headwater catchments and returns a data.frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#' with the current ID and the feature ID it should collapse into (becomes).

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#' Headwaters are segments in which there are no inflows (!ID %in% toID).

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#' @param network_list  a list containing flowpath and catchment `sf` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_area_sqkm The minimum allowable size of the output hydrofabric catchments

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_length_km The minimum allowable length of the output hydrofabric flowlines

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a 2 column data.frame with {id, becomes}

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr mutate filter group_by mutate ungroup distinct

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom sf st_set_geometry st_geometry st_buffer st_intersects

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom nhdplusTools get_node

                    		
                  

                  

                    50

build_collapse_table = function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
                                min_area_sqkm  = 3,

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
                                min_length_km  = 1) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
  # are fps junctions, if so who do they touch?

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
  touch_id <-  define_touch_id(flowpaths = network_list$flowpaths) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(type == "jun") %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(id != touches)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
  # bad fps are those that are both hw and too small or too large

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
  bad =  mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list$flowpaths,

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
    hw = ifelse(!id %in% toid, TRUE, FALSE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
    small = areasqkm < min_area_sqkm | lengthkm < min_length_km

                    		
                  

                  

                    66

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(hw, small) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
    st_cast("MULTILINESTRING")

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
  filter(touch_id, touches == 36112)

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
  # bad outlets

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
  outlets =  st_buffer(st_set_geometry(bad, st_geometry(get_node(bad, "end"))), 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
  # intersect bad outlets with fp network

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
  emap = st_intersects(outlets, network_list$flowpaths)

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
  df = data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
    #bad outlet ID

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    id       = rep(outlets$id, times = lengths(emap)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
    #bad outlet topo toID

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
    toid     = rep(outlets$toid, times = lengths(emap)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
    # bad outlets touches

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
    touches  = network_list$flowpaths$id[unlist(emap)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
    # we dont care if it touches itself

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(!.data$id == .data$touches) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
    # group_by ID

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
    group_by(id) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
    # If the bad fp touches is topo toid, the bad id will become the min (most downstream) toid or the id it touches (most downstream)

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(becomes = ifelse(any(toid == touches), min(toid), min(touches))) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
    ungroup()   %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(!id %in% becomes) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
    select(id, becomes) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    distinct()

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp_id = filter(touch_id, touches %in% df$id) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
    select(id, becomes = touches) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
    group_by(becomes) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
    slice_min(id) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
    ungroup()

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp_id2 = tmp_id %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    left_join(touch_id, by = c('becomes' = 'id')) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(is.na(type))

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
  df = df %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(!id %in% tmp_id$becomes) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
    bind_rows(tmp_id2) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
    select(id, becomes) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
    distinct() 

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
  df$mC1 = network_list$flowpaths$member_comid[match(df$id, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
  df$mC2 = network_list$flowpaths$member_comid[match(df$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
  df$poi1 = network_list$flowpaths$poi_id[match(df$id, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
  df$poi2 = network_list$flowpaths$poi_id[match(df$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
  suppressWarnings({

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
    group_by(df, becomes) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate(member_comid = paste0(mC2[1], "," ,paste(mC1, collapse = ",")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
             poi_id = as.numeric(paste(unique(na.omit(c(poi1, poi2))), collapse = ","))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    123

      ungroup() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    124

      select(-mC1, -mC2, -poi1, -poi2)

  })

}

#' Collapse Headwaters

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
#' @description  This function identifies small (pathlength or area) headwater catchments and

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
#' collapses them into the existing network until none remain.

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
#' Headwaters are those segments in which there are no inflows (!ID %in% toID).

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
#' @param network_list  a list containing flowpath and catchment `sf` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_area_sqkm The minimum allowable size of the output hydrofabric catchments

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_length_km The minimum allowable length of the output hydrofabric flowlines

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#' @param verbose should messages be emitted?

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
#' @param cache_file If not NULL results will be written to a provide path (.gpkg)

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a list containing flowpath and catchment `sf` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr filter left_join mutate bind_rows

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom nhdplusTools get_node

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
collapse_headwaters = function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
                               min_area_sqkm  = 3,

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
                               min_length_km  = 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
                               verbose = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
                               cache_file = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
  hyaggregate_log("INFO", "\n--- Collapse Network Inward ---\n", verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
  start <- nrow(network_list$flowpaths)

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
  mapping_table <- build_collapse_table(network_list, min_area_sqkm, min_length_km)

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
  count = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
  while (nrow(mapping_table) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
    count = count + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
    hyaggregate_log("INFO", glue("Collapsing: {nrow(mapping_table)} features (round {count})"), verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
    ind = match(mapping_table$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list$flowpaths$member_comid[ind] = mapping_table$member_comid

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
    fl = filter(network_list$flowpaths, !id %in% mapping_table$id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
    cat = filter(network_list$catchments,

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    !
                    
                      
                 id %in% c(mapping_table$id, mapping_table$becomes)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    !
                    
                      
      left_join(mapping_table, by = "id") |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate(id = ifelse(is.na(becomes), id, becomes)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    !
                    
                      
      union_polygons("id") |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
      bind_rows(filter(

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !
                    
                      
        select(network_list$catchments, id),

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
        !id %in% c(mapping_table$id, mapping_table$becomes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
      )) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
      left_join(st_drop_geometry(select(fl, id, toid)), by = "id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list  = prepare_network(network_list = list(flowpaths = fl, catchments = cat))

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(fl, !(fl$toid %in% fl$id | fl$toid > term_cut | fl$toid == 0))

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(fl, id == 48486)

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
    mapping_table = build_collapse_table(network_list, min_area_sqkm, min_length_km)

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
  hyaggregate_log("SUCCESS", glue("Collapsed {start - nrow(network_list$flowpaths)} features."), verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(cache_file)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
    write_hydrofabric(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
                      cache_file,

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
                      "collapse_headwaters_catchments",

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    !
                    
                      
                      "collapse_headwaters_flowpaths",

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    !
                    
                      
                      verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    !
                    
                      
  return(network_list)

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Aggregate along network mainstems

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Given a set of ideal catchment sizes, plus the

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' minimum allowable catchment size and segment length, aggregate the network along mainstems.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param network_list a list containing flowline and catchment `sf` objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ideal_size The ideal size of output hydrofabric catchments

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_area_sqkm The minimum allowable size of the output hydrofabric catchments

                    		
                  

                  

                    7

aggregate_along_mainstems = function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
                                     ideal_size_sqkm,

                                     min_area_sqkm,

                                     verbose = TRUE,

                    24
                    !

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
  hyaggregate_log("INFO", glue("min_length_km --> {min_length_km}"),     verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
  hyaggregate_log("INFO", glue("min_area_sqkm --> {min_area_sqkm}"),     verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28

                    !
                    
                      
  tmp = network_list$flowpaths %>%

    st_drop_geometry() %>%

    st_drop_geometry() %>%

    distinct() %>%

    ungroup()

  fline = network_list$flowpaths %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    40

    st_drop_geometry() %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    41

    mutate(poi_dn = poi_id) %>%

    left_join(tmp, by = "id") %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
    distinct() 

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
  index_table = fline %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
    group_by(.data$levelpathid) %>%

    arrange(.data$hydroseq) %>%

    mutate(poi_un = ifelse(poi_un %in% poi_dn, NA, poi_un)) %>%

    mutate(

      ind = cs_group(

        .data$areasqkm,

        .data$poi_un,

        min_area_sqkm,

                  glue("Merged to idealized catchment size of {ideal_size_sqkm} sqkm: {nrow(network_list$flowpaths) - nrow(v$flowpaths)} features removed"),
