#' Cumulative sum area grouping

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function takes a vector of areas and lengths and returns a

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' index vector that combines them towards an ideal aggregate area (ideal_size_sqkm). While enforcing a minimum area (amin) and length (lmin).

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
#' Additionally, this function can take a set of indexes to exclude over which the network cannot be aggregated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
#' @param areas a vector of areas

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lengths a vector of lengths

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
#' @param exclude_dn a vector of equal length to areas and lengths. Any non NA value will be used to enforce an aggregation break on the outflow node of a flowpath

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
#' @param exclude_un a vector of equal length to areas and lengths. Any non NA value will be used to enforce an aggregation break on the inflow node of a flowpath

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ideal_size_sqkm a vector of areas

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
#' @param amin a threshold, or target, cumulative size

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lmin a threshold, or target, cumulative size

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a vector of length(areas) containing grouping indexes

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
cs_group <- function(areas, lengths, exclude_dn, exclude_un, ideal_size_sqkm, amin, lmin) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
  areas[is.na(areas)] = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
  lengths[is.na(lengths)] = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(areas) == 1){ return(1) }

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
  break_index = which(!is.na(exclude_dn))

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
  break_index2 = which(!is.na(exclude_un)) - 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
  break_index = sort(c(break_index, break_index2))

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(break_index) != 0){

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
    sub_areas = splitAt(areas, break_index)

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
    sub_lengths = splitAt(lengths, break_index)

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
    sub_areas = list(areas)

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
    sub_lengths = list(lengths)

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
  if(all(lengths(sub_areas) != lengths(sub_lengths))){

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
    stop("Yuck~")

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
  o1 = lapply(sub_areas, assign_id, athres = ideal_size_sqkm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
  o2 = lapply(1:length(sub_areas),   function(i) { pinch_sides(   x = sub_areas[[i]],   ind = o1[[i]], thres = amin) })

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
  o3 = lapply(1:length(sub_lengths), function(i) { pinch_sides(   x = sub_lengths[[i]], ind = o2[[i]], thres = lmin) })

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
  o4 = lapply(1:length(sub_areas),   function(i) { middle_massage(x = sub_areas[[i]],   ind = o3[[i]], thres = amin) })

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
  o5 = lapply(1:length(sub_lengths), function(i) { middle_massage(x = sub_lengths[[i]], ind = o4[[i]], thres = lmin) })

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    !
                    
                      
  for(i in 1:length(o5)){ o5[[i]] = o5[[i]] + 1e9*i }

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
  unlist(o5)

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
#' Re-index the edges of vector by threshold

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#' Merge the outside edges of a vector if they are less then the provides threshold.

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x vector of values

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ind current index values

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#' @param thres threshold to evaluate x

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a vector of length(x) containing grouping indexes

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
pinch_sides = function(x, ind, thres){

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp_areas = unlist(lapply(split(x, ind), sum))

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(tmp_areas) == 1){ return(ind) }

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
  n = as.numeric(names(tmp_areas))

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
  if(tmp_areas[1] < thres){

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
    names(tmp_areas)[1] = names(tmp_areas[2])

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
  if(tmp_areas[length(tmp_areas)] < thres){

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
    names(tmp_areas)[length(tmp_areas)] = names(tmp_areas[length(tmp_areas) - 1])

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
  n2 = as.numeric(names(tmp_areas))

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
  n2[match(ind, n)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
#' @title Re-index the interior of vector by threshold

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
#' @description  Merges the interior values of a vector if they are less then the provided threshold.

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
#' Merging will look "up" and "down" the vector and merge into the smaller of the two.

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x vector of values

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
#' @param index_values current index values

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
#' @param threshold threshold to evaluate x

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a vector of length(x) containing grouping indexes

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
middle_massage = function(x, index_values, threshold){

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
  tmp_areas = unlist(lapply(split(x, index_values), sum))

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(tmp_areas) == 1){ return(index_values) }

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
  n = as.numeric(names(tmp_areas))

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    !
                    
                      
  if(any(tmp_areas < threshold)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
    tmp = which(tmp_areas < threshold)

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
    for(j in 1:length(tmp)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
      base = as.numeric(tmp[j])

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
      edges = c(base - 1, base + 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
      becomes = names(which.min(tmp_areas[edges]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    !
                    
                      
      names(tmp_areas)[base] = becomes

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    !
                    
                      
  n2 = as.numeric(names(tmp_areas))

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
  n2[match(index_values, n)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      
#' Enforces area and length grouping

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function takes a vector of area's and length's and returns a

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      
#' grouping vector that enforces the grouping of lengths and areas less then defined thresholds

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    
                    
                      
#' @param l a vector of lengths

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    
                    
                      
#' @param a a vector of areas

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lthres a minimum length that must be achieved

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
#' @param athres a minimum length that must be achieved

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a vector of length(a) containing grouping indexes

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    
                    
                      
agg_length_area   <- function(l, a, lthres, athres) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    !
                    
                      
  ids = 1:length(l)

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    !
                    
                      
  if(length(ids) != 1){

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    !
                    
                      
    if(!is.null(lthres)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    !
                    
                      
      for (i in 1:(length(l)-1)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    !
                    
                      
        if (l[i] < lthres) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    !
                    
                      
          ids[(i+1):length(l)] = ids[(i+1):length(l)] - 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    !
                    
                      
          l[i+1] = l[i] + l[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    !
                    
                      
          l[i]   = l[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    !
                    
                      
          a[i+1] = a[i] + a[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    !
                    
                      
          a[i] =   a[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    !
                    
                      
    if(!is.null(athres)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    !
                    
                      
      for (i in 1:(length(a)-1)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    !
                    
                      
        if (a[i] < athres) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    !
                    
                      
          ids[(i+1):length(a)] = ids[(i+1):length(a)] - 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    !
                    
                      
          a[i+1] = a[i] + a[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    !
                    
                      
          a[i] =   a[i+1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    !
                    
                      
    if(is.null(athres)){ athres = 0 }

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    !
                    
                      
    if(is.null(lthres)){ lthres = 0 }

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    !
                    
                      
    if(a[length(a)] < athres | l[length(l)] < lthres){

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    !
                    
                      
      ids[length(ids)] = pmax(1, ids[length(ids)] - 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    !
                    
                      
  return (ids)

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    
                    
                      
#' Split a Vector as a position

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x vector of values

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    
                    
                      
#' @param pos split postion

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    
                    
                      
splitAt <- function(x, pos) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    !
                    
                      
  unname(split(x, cumsum(seq_along(x) %in% (pos + 1)) ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    
                    
                      
#' Index a Vector by Cumulative Sum

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x a vector of values

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    
                    
                      
#' @param athres the ideal cumulative size of each group

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      
#' Cumulative sums will get as close to this value without exceeding it

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      
#' @return a vector of length(a)

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    
                    
                      
assign_id = function(x, athres){

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    !
                    
                      
  cumsum <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    !
                    
                      
  group  <- 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    !
                    
                      
  result <- numeric()

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    !
                    
                      
  for (i in 1:length(x)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    !
                    
                      
    cumsum <- cumsum + x[i]

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    !
                    
                      
    if (cumsum > athres) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    !
                    
                      
      group <- group + 1

poi_to_outlet = function(gpkg,

                    1x

                    1x

add_mapped_pois = function(network_list, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
                           refactored_gpkg = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
                           verbose = TRUE){

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
  generate_mapped_pois = filter(network_list$flowpaths, !is.na(poi_id)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    select(id, poi_id) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
    st_cast("MULTILINESTRING")

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
  mapped_POIs = st_set_geometry(generate_mapped_pois,

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
                                                 st_geometry(get_node(generate_mapped_pois,

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
                                                                      position = "end" )))

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    112

                    113
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    114

  if(!is.null(refactored_gpkg)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    116

                    117

      st_drop_geometry()  %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate_at(vars(matches("Type_")), as.character) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate(poi_id = as.character(identifier),

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
             identifier = NULL) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(ID, poi_id) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    !
                    
                      
      ungroup() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
      pivot_longer(-c(poi_id, ID)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !

                    126
                    !

                    127

                    132

                    134

generate_lookup_table = function(gpkg = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
                                 refactored_gpkg = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
                                 reconciled_layer = "flowpaths") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    2x
                    
                      
  if(is.null(gpkg) & !is.null(refactored_gpkg)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    164

                    165
                    1x

                    166
                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

                    183

  if (is.null(gpkg) | is.null(refactored_gpkg)) {

#' @title Aggregate Network to Uniform Size

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function aggregates a network to a desired size distribution while

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' enforcing minimum flowpath legnths and catchment areas. Additionally a set of explicit nexus

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' locations can be provided over which the network cannot be aggregated (see poi_to_outlet)

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param gpkg a path to a gpkg

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param divide If gpkg is NULL, then an sf data.frame, otherwise a the layer name. See details.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param flowpath If gpkg is NULL, then an sf data.frame, otherwise a the layer name. See details.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outlets data.frame with mandatory "ID" column and optional "POI_ID" column. "ID" must be identifiers from

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' flowpath and divide data.frames and POI ID must be unique.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ideal_size_sqkm The ideal size of catchments (default = 10 sqkm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_length_km The minimum allowable length of flowpath features (default = 1 km)

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_area_sqkm The minimum allowable area of catchment features (default = 3 sqkm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param outfile of not NULL, where to write the output files

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param overwrite overwrite existing gf file. Default is FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param nexus_locations a data.frame with columns specifying the ID, and the nexus type.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param log a filepath to write messages to or Boolean (TRUE = print to console; FALSE = no messages)

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @param verbose print status updates. Default = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @return if outfile = TRUE, a file path, else a list object

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @details If gpkg is not NULL, divide and flowpath can be left NULL as well. The code attempts to

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' infer the correct layers. The divides layer will be the one including the word "divide" or "catchment" and the

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' flowpath layer will be the one including 'flowpath' or 'flowline'. If no layers, or more then one layer are deemed possible

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' for each input, then the function will stop and ask for explicit names.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom sf st_transform read_sf st_set_crs write_sf st_layers

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr left_join filter

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom nhdplusTools get_sorted calculate_total_drainage_area get_streamorder

#' @importFrom logger log_appender appender_file appender_console

Choose accordingly:\n        Windows: https://www.7-zip.org/download.html\n        Mac: 'brew install p7zip' or 'sudo port install p7zip'\n        Linux: https://sourceforge.net/projects/p7zip/"))

#' Download Elevation and Derivatives

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param product character DEM, hydroDEM, or FDRFAC.  

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param out_dir path to directory to store output.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param regions character vector of two digit hydrologic 

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom rvest read_html html_nodes html_attr

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr RETRY write_disk progress

                    		
                  

                  

                    16

                    17
                    
                    
                      
download_elev <- function(product, out_dir, regions = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
  dev_null <- check7z()

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
  allowable <- c("DEM" = ".*NEDSnapshot.*", "hydroDEM" = ".*HydroDem.*", "FDRFAC" = ".*FdrFac.*")

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
  if(!all(product %in% names(allowable))) stop(paste("product must be one of", allowable))

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
  dir.create(out_dir, recursive = TRUE, showWarnings = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
  root <- "http://www.horizon-systems.com"

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
  base <- "/NHDPlusData/NHDPlusV21/Data/"

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
  check <- paste0(root, base)

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
  found <- c()

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
  i <- 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
  while(i <= length(check)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    url <- check[i]

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
    pg <- rvest::read_html(url)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
    pg_links <- paste0(url, html_attr(html_nodes(pg, "a"), "href"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
    pg_links <- pg_links[!pg_links %in% check]

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
    check <- c(check, pg_links[!grepl("[.][.]/", pg_links) & grepl(".*/$", pg_links)])

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
    found <- c(found, pg_links[grepl(paste(allowable[product], collapse = "|"), pg_links, ignore.case = TRUE)])

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
    i <- i + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
    if(i > 10000) stop("something is wrong with the URL finder loop.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
  if(!is.null(regions)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
    found <- found[grepl(paste(paste0(".*_", regions, "?[a-z]_.*"), 

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
                               collapse = "|"), found, ignore.case = TRUE)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
  for(f in found) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
    fi <- basename(f)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
    url <- f

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
    out_fi <- file.path(out_dir, fi)

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    message(out_fi)

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
    if(!file.exists(out_fi)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
      RETRY("GET", url, write_disk(out_fi), progress())

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
      system(paste0("7z -y -o", path.expand(out_dir), " x ", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
                    path.expand(out_fi)), intern = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
}

build_headwater_collapse = function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
                                    min_area_sqkm  = 3,

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
                                    min_length_km  = 1) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    !
                    
                      
  touch_id <-  define_touch_id(flowpaths = network_list$flowpaths) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(type == "jun") %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(id != touches)

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
  # bad fps are those that are both hw and too small or too large

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    !
                    
                      
  df =  mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list$flowpaths,

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    !
                    
                      
    inflow = ifelse(id %in% touch_id$touches, TRUE, FALSE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    !
                    
                      
    hw = ifelse(!id %in% toid, TRUE, FALSE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    !
                    
                      
    hw = ifelse(hw & !inflow, TRUE, FALSE),

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    !
                    
                      
    small = areasqkm < min_area_sqkm | lengthkm < min_length_km

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  ) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(hw, small) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
    st_drop_geometry() %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    !
                    
                      
    select(id, becomes = toid, member_comid, poi_id) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(becomes != 0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
  df$mC1 = network_list$flowpaths$member_comid[match(df$id, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
  df$mC2 = network_list$flowpaths$member_comid[match(df$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
  df$poi1 = network_list$flowpaths$poi_id[match(df$id, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
  df$poi2 = network_list$flowpaths$poi_id[match(df$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
  suppressWarnings({

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
    group_by(df, becomes) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate(member_comid = paste0(mC2[1], "," ,paste(mC1, collapse = ",")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
             poi_id = as.numeric(paste(unique(na.omit(c(poi1, poi2))), collapse = ","))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
      ungroup() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
      select(-mC1, -mC2, -poi1, -poi2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    39

collapse_headwaters2 = function(network_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
                               min_area_sqkm  = 3,

                    		
                  

                  

                    44

                    45
                    
                    
                      
                               verbose = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
                               cache_file = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !

                    50
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
  start <- nrow(network_list$flowpaths)

                    53

                    55

  count = 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    57

  while (nrow(mapping_table) > 0) {

                    59

    count = count + 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    60

    ind = match(mapping_table$becomes, network_list$flowpaths$id)

    fl = filter(network_list$flowpaths, !id %in% mapping_table$id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
    cat = filter(network_list$catchments,

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
                 id %in% c(mapping_table$id, mapping_table$becomes)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
      left_join(mapping_table, by = "id") |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
      mutate(id = ifelse(is.na(becomes), id, becomes)) |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
      union_polygons("id") |>

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
      bind_rows(filter(

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
        select(network_list$catchments, id),

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
        !id %in% c(mapping_table$id, mapping_table$becomes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
      )) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
      left_join(st_drop_geometry(select(fl, id, toid)), by = "id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    network_list  = prepare_network(network_list = list(flowpaths = fl, catchments = cat))

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
    mapping_table = build_headwater_collapse(network_list, min_area_sqkm, min_length_km)

                    84
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    85

  hyaggregate_log("SUCCESS", glue("Collapsed {start - nrow(network_list$flowpaths)} features."), verbose)

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(cache_file)) {
